@startuml unlikePost
!include ../../theme/theme-dark-seq.puml

title unlikePost flow
actor User
participant Resolver
participant PostsService as P
participant LikesService as L
participant ActivityService as A
database DB

User -> Resolver: unlikePost()
Resolver -> P: unlikePost() : bool

group postsRepo.manager.transaction
  P -> DB: manager.findOne(User)
  DB --> P: user

  P -> DB: lockEntityByIdOrThrow(Post) + load user relation
  DB --> P: post

  P -> L: unlike()
  L -> DB: repo.findOne()
  DB --> L: like | null

  note over L,P
  Overall flow:
  - if no active like exists, return success immediately
  - otherwise deactivate the like
  -- then log post-like activity as inactive
  end note

  alt no active like exists
    L --> P: changed = false
    P -> P: skip activity log (idempotent)
  else like state changed
    L -> DB: repo.save() [active=true -> false]
    DB --> L: like deactivated
    L --> P: changed = true

    P -> A: logActivity()
    A -> DB: repo.query()
    DB --> A: activity row
    A --> P: activity
  end
end

P --> Resolver: true
Resolver --> User: data.unlikePost = true

== Error rule ==
note over P,DB
If any awaited step inside the transaction throws:
TypeORM issues ROLLBACK, then error bubbles to resolver,
and resolver returns a GraphQL error.
end note
@enduml
